</tbody></table>
<p>=3D 4 ( 2 - 3 ) - 3 ( 1 - 6 ) + 9 ( 1 - 4 )  =3D 4 ( -1 ) - 3 ( -5 ) + 9=
 ( -3
  )  =3D -4 + 15 - 27 =3D -16</p>
<p>Consider the other 3=D73 matrix. In this one, there is a 0 in the row
  1 and column 2. Either one of those would be a good pick for expansion, b=
ut
  since row 1 has slightly larger numbers, we'll expand along the first row=
.</p>
<table border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"1" cellspacing=3D"0">
  <tbody><tr>
    <td class=3D"detl">3</td>
    <td class=3D"lhs">0</td>
    <td class=3D"detr">1</td>
    <td class=3D"lhs">&nbsp;</td>
    <td class=3D"lhs">&nbsp;</td>
    <td class=3D"lhs">&nbsp;</td>
    <td class=3D"lhs">&nbsp;</td>
    <td class=3D"lhs">&nbsp;</td>
    <td class=3D"lhs">&nbsp;</td>
    <td class=3D"lhs">&nbsp;</td>
    <td class=3D"lhs">&nbsp;</td>
